method.description:
Message attributes:

@filename (symbol, default: none): filename

@dpi (int, default: 72): Dots Per Inch

@width (double, default: none): Width In Coordinates

@height (double, default: none): Height In Coordinates

@pixelwidth (double, default: none): Width In Pixels

@pixelheight (double, default: none): Height In Pixels

@center (llll, default: none): Center Coordinates

@zoom (llll, default: none): Zoom Percentage



Saves the object as a PNG image. Optional argument provides the filename (otherwise a dialog box will pop up).

The word exportpng, followed by an file path, exports the current canvas as a PNG image.
This can be further followed by a list formatted as:
(specification value) (specification value).... 

Each specification can be one of the followings: 

• "dpi": the value is expected to be the dpi resolution of the exported image; 

• "width": the value is expected to be the width of the exported image in pixels; 

• "height": the value is expected to be the height of the exported image in pixels; 

• "center": the value is expected to be an llll containing the coordinates of the center;
